<example-descriptor>
    <title>OPS Forms Example</title>
    <xi:include href="example-descriptor-files.xml" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2003/XInclude"/>
    <description xmlns:f="http://orbeon.org/oxf/xml/formatting">
        <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
            <p>
                This example handles web forms with XForms. It illustrates some best practices of
                XForms and Orbeon Presentation Server, among others:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>Using XForms to represent and display form data.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Using XForms's XML Schema support to validate form data.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Using XForms to retrieve and save data from XML services.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Using <code>xforms:repeat</code> to repeat homogeneous data sections.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Producing forms in different formats such as HTML, XML or PDF.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Implementing XML services quickly with the Page Flow Controler, XPL and the eXist XML database.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Navigating between pages with page flow and XForms.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Externalizing resources to facilitate maintenance and localization.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </description>
</example-descriptor>
